ake it more difficult for people to move out of poverty. At the same time the framework for understanding the governance structures, enactment practices, and social wealth leverage presented in Privatizing the Polity offers numerous opportunities for acquiring a deeper understanding of assumptions formerly taken for granted and redirecting the system to enhance poverty alleviation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aEconomic assistance, DomesticxUnited States. 0aEconomic assistance, DomesticzUnited States. 0aPovertyxGovernment policyxUnited States. 0aPovertyxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aPrivatizationxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aPrivatizationzUnited States. 4aPolitics and Law : American Government. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 4aSociology : Social Problems. 4aSociology : Social Stratification. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Economic Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2015z978311149061840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845761140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438457611423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438457611/original  a978-3-11-149061-8  SUNY Press eBook Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles